Welcome to the 2020-21 school year. We are looking forward to welcoming your child back to school this fall and are committed to providing the best educational and social/emotional learning experience possible. We know you have many questions as we navigate what school will look like this year. We‚Äôre hoping this document will help answer your questions. This information is what we know now, but it may change as guidance from the Indiana State Department of Health or the Pulaski County Health Department is modified. Because this remains an evolving situation, we will continue to provide updates about necessary plan adjustments. Our goal is to keep you fully informed as we navigate this school year together.

Click here to see the 2020-2021 Reopening Plan: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Huan-8zl5YpiopWou98JcvRg5TcRAhzV/view

With many schools returning, we have decided to offer spiritwear face coverings. These masks are 3 ply construction - layers made of soft B- core moisture management. Comfort anti-chafe ear loops that stretch 100% and hold their shape while being soft on the ear for all day wear. Middle seam contours and conforms to the face. Durable lab tested fabrics and are washable. These mask come in 15 stylish colors and sizes start from youth small/medium and go all the way thru adult. Blank masks start at 7 dollars and customized masks are 10 dollars.

GRADUATION UPDATE:
Governor Holcomb stated that starting July 4th the state of Indiana is expected to enter Stage 5 of his plan to get Indiana back on track. With that in mind, EPCSC is lifting the limit of 4 guests per each graduating senior at our graduation ceremony on July 10th. Bleacher space will be limited so families are encouraged to bring lawn chairs. EPCSC continues to encourage following social distancing guidelines and recommends individuals with known high-risk medical conditions to remain cautious in social situations.

Coach Hendryx brings a 217-93 record in 27 seasons that includes 1 state championship, 2 semi state championships, and sectional wins at 3 different schools. We are excited to welcome you Mr. Hendryx! #WarriorPride

post_text:
Because of the continuing COVID-19 crisis, the Indiana Department of Education and Governor Holcomb have directed all schools to close through the end of this academic school year. Our EPCSC school buildings will be closed, but our extended eLearning will continue through the end of the school year. We are saddened by this news, but the safety of our students, staff, and community remain our top priority.

We will provide additional information to you after receiving more information and guidance from the Indiana Department of Education.

Please continue to practice social distancing and remain quarantined in order to reduce the spread of the virus and remain healthy and safe.

EPCSC will be closed beginning Monday, March 16th due to the COVID-19 virus threat. Please check our website www.epulaski.k12.in.us for updated information. The plan is as follows:
* March 14- scheduled eLearning makeup
* March 16- No school, waiver day
* March 17-20 - eLearning days
* March 23-27 - Spring Break
* March 30 - April 3 - No school, waiver days

We will continue to update information as it become available. We appreciate your understanding and support as we work to keep our students, staff, and community safe.

There has been consideration concerning tomorrow's planned e-learning day. It is my understanding that this plan and policy was adopted last year as an agreed upon way of transitioning into meaningful e-learning days. The unanticipated weather highlights the need to get this right as policy adjustments are made concerning e-learning in the future. Therefore, the planned e-learning day is still in effect for tomorrow.

Dr. Crimmins

post_text:
Recently, a number of longtime EP employees retired and we want to thank them again for their years of dedicated service to the students of Eastern Pulaski!!! We wish you a fond farewell and enjoy your much-deserved retirement!!

Mrs. Pam Burger--38 years at EP and 41 years total!
Mrs. Lynn Darda--28 years at EP and 32 years total!
Mrs. Jane Dilts--34 years at EP and 43 years total!
Mrs. Barb Hickle--41 years all at EP and all in 2nd grade!
Mr. Leo Hummel (not pictured)--15 years at EP and 42 years total!
Mr. George Nietert (not pictured)--32 years at EP and 42 years total!
Mrs. Candi Reutebuch (not pictured)--EP school bus driver for 33 years!

That is 221 years of service to the students of Eastern Pulaski! Thank you and well done!

*Thank you Amber Tomlinson and Pulaski County Journal for allowing use of the pictures.

shared_text:
Frain Mortuary
June 4, 2019 at 2:09 PM ¬∑

Special thanks to Winamac High School for allowing our local funeral directors (Dan and Jon) to help educate the students on important life topics!

Dan taught several classes at the Funeral Home on funerals, preplanning, burial and cremation.

Jon taught several classes at the School on Distracted Driving.

The students were very receptive and well mannered.

Thank You Winamac High School for allowing us to be a small part of our kids‚Äô education.

Eastern Pulaski Community School Corporation

May 23, 2019 at 10:22 AM ¬∑

Winamac Community High School names top graduates
Winamac Community High School is pleased to announce its top two graduates for the 2018-19 school year.
Jennifer Budd, daughter of Dave and Karen Budd, has been named the valedictorian and Jillian Brumm, daughter of Bryce and Lori Brumm, is the salutatorian.
See the full story in the Pulaski County Journal, available in print and online for digital subscribers.
